definition.value: A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of any bacteriochlorophyll e.
A chlorophyllide in which two of the methyl hydrogens at position 7 of any bacteriochlorophyllide c have been replaced by hydroxy groups.
A member of the class of benzaldehydes carrying hydroxy and methoxy substituents at positions 2 and 5 respectively.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid in which a benzoic acid nucleus is substituted at positions 2 and 5 by a formyl group and an hydroxy group  respectively.
A fatty acyl-AMP that results from the formal condensation of the phosphoryl group of AMP with the carboxyl group of any long-chain fatty acid.
An acyclic mixed acid anhydride obtained by condensation of one of the carboxy group of pyridinium-3,5-biscarboxylic acid mononucleotide with the phosphste group of AMP.
An acyclic mixed acid anhydride obtained by condensation of one of the carboxy group of pyridinium-3-sulfanylcarbonyl-5-carboxylic acid mononucleotide with the phosphste group of AMP.
1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group at position 1 is specified as hexanoyl.
A 1-palmitoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 2-acyl group is specified as (11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatrienoyl.
A calcium salt containing equal numbers of prohexadione(2-) and Ca(2+) ions. A plant growth regulator, it is used as an anti-lodging agent in small-grain cereals.
The ketoaldonic acid phosphate formed formally from D-erythronic acid by oxidation of the 3-hydroxy group to an oxo group and phosphorylation at the 1-hydroxy group.

The hydrate of tetrahydroxy-1,4-benzoquinone. The number of water molecules of crystallization (n) is variable, although most commonly the dihydrate (shown in the diagram) is formed in the solid phase.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as (11R)-hydroxy-(5Z,8Z,12E,14Z)-icosatetraenoyl.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as (15R)-hydroxy-(5Z,8Z,11Z,13E)-icosatetraenoyl.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as (15S)-hydroxy-(5Z,8Z,11Z,13E)-icosatetraenoyl.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as (5Z,13E,15S)-11alpha,15-dihydroxy-9-oxoprosta-5,13-dien-1-oyl
An aminobenzoate that is the conjugate base of 4-aminosalicylic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major miscrospecies at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of pteroates that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxy-7,8-dihydropteroic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
